# IP Addresses

An IP address identifies a device on a network.

Every device connected to the internet requires an IP address.

Examples:
- Computers
- Phones
- Routers
- Servers

IPv4 Example:
192.168.1.1

IPv6 Example:
2001:db8::1

Why it matters in cybersecurity:

Attackers often target IP addresses to:
- Scan networks
- Discover devices
- Launch attacks

Network administrators use IP addresses to monitor and secure networks.
